<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

   If someone here at Verant wants to answer that guy's essay, then Chris
is in luck.  That someone won't be me, though; I'm not qualified to answer
him.  Heck, even if I was qualified, I probably wouldn't be permitted to
do so.  Anyone familiar with this site knows (or should know) that I'm
an *artist*, and that the only detailed questions about EverQuest that I
can be expected to answer will pertain to the game's graphics.<P>

   I get questions irrelevant to the nature of Ask Milo all the time: stuff
like
"hey man can you tell me the best place fer a ranger to level up ten times
in an hour, thanks" and "where can I get a skull staff the easy way" and
"what's the best character to play if I wanna run somebody through with
a sword and then fry 'em with a lightning bolt" and "I have a neat idea to
make your game more funner."  I suspect that most of these e-mails come
from people who seek to take advantage of this site as some kind of
conduit to any Verant personnel with the power to provide satisfaction.<P>

   I appreciated Chris' effort, but Ask Milo has never, ever been a place
for people to vent about EQ's game play (or to make suggestions for it,
or to ask me where to get rare weaponry, etc.).  This site is for *graphics*
questions (as is quite clearly stated at the top of the page) and off-beat
discussion.  Submit anything else at your own risk, people.</font></td>
